Operation Instructions Insert the power 20-pin or 24-pin and P4, P6 or P8 plug into the corresponding position of the power tester. (if 20pin or 24pin connector sets off an alarm and displays “LL”, it needs to plug in 4P connector. )Turn on the power supply, at the same time, and there will be two beeps. If the values of each group do not flash, it indicates that the power input of this power supply is normal.The voltage of IDE / SATA / P6 / P8 interface is displayed by the three lights on the left of the power tester. If their voltage is normal, the three groups of lights (+ 12V, + 3.3, + 5V) will be on. If the light is not on, it indicates that the interface line group is faulty.If the voltage signal of a circuit is not detected (such as 20-pin or 24-pin connector) or the detected voltage exceeds the normal range, the tester will send out a warning sound of two beeps for a long time, and the corresponding voltage or PG value display status is flashing state, it means that the power supply is a fault source!Special reminder: The power supply tester does not support hot-plug

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Honestly worth it for the price!
reviews.reviewText: It works amazing! It’s handy and it’s worth the price!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great little tester to validate your power supply is working.
reviews.reviewText: This tester saved me more than once. I had a particularly difficult build where the attached peripherals needing power were questionable. I removed all devices and slowly added them and the tester confirmed that power was being generated and the quality of that power. This is a really handy tester to own and use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It takes the guesswork out of power supply voltage and related issues. It's featherlight but still has a sturdy aluminum housing. Invaluable if you area refurbishing and testing PC's and PSU's.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Compact and Useful
reviews.reviewText: Was able to check new and old power supply. Have to remember to plug in main board or wide plug to check smaller plugs (4-6-8). Didn't see how to check SATA power lines but good tool to tell you if power supply has gone bad.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Tested a used power supply I bought using this - showed all the relevant values and my PSU has been working perfectly with no issue. Thanks Kingwin!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2023

reviews.reviewText: I tested a Dead Power supply and as expected No out put.When I tested a known good power supply all the voltages were displayed.Happy with my purchase. with a quick easy way of determining what condition a power supply is.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I liked how easy this thing is to use, and how accurate it is. I used it on a Game Max 850W Power Supply.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023

reviews.reviewText: I can't believe I have done PC repair without one of these. It is super handy, but don't lose the instructions, they are necessary to refer back to on how to use it.
